.Sh STANDARDS
These signals conform to
.St -p1003.1-90 ,
with the exception of
.Dv SIGTRAP ,
.Dv SIGEMT ,
.Dv SIGBUS ,
.Dv SIGSYS ,
.Dv SIGURG ,
.Dv SIGIO ,
.Dv SIGXCPU ,
.Dv SIGXFSZ ,
.Dv SIGVTALRM ,
.Dv SIGPROF ,
.Dv SIGWINCH ,
and
.Dv SIGINFO
which are Berkeley extensions (available on most
.Bx Ns \-derived
systems), and
.Dv SIGPWR
which comes from System V.
.Sh HISTORY
.Dv SIGPWR
was introduced in
.Nx 1.4 .
.Sh NOTES
The current
.Nx
kernel never generates the
.Dv SIGPWR
signal.
